t"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lay of the Children of Húrin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lays of Beleriand"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tolkien"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Túrin"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Arrows"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Axes"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Bows"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Knives"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Maces"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Spears"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Swords"}, {"ns": 14, "exists": "", "*": "Category:Weapons"}], "templates": [{"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:References"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:LB"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:PE"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:HH"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Weapons"}], "images": ["Marya_Filatova_-_Archers_-_Beleg.jpg"], "wikitext": {"*": "[[File:Marya Filatova - Archers - Beleg.jpg|thumb|250px|''Archers - Beleg'' by [[Marya Filatova]]]]\n'''Dailir''' was the name of the arrow used by [[Beleg|Beleg Strongbow]] with his bow, [[Belthronding]]. After shooting this arrow Beleg always found it unharmed. However, it was broken at last when Beleg fell upon it when he was carrying [[Túrin]].<ref name=Dailir>{{LB|1c}}, vv. 1080-1083, 1187-1192</ref> This arrow is only featured in the first version of ''[[The Lay of the Children of Húrin]]''.<ref>{{LB|1}}, Commentary on ''Part II 'Beleg''', p. 53</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\n''dailir'' is glossed \"cleaver\" in the Noldorin Word-lists, and is related to the [[Noldorin]] verb ''daila-'' (\"to cleave\") and the noun ''dail'' (\"axe-blade\"). The ''-ir'' suffix creates an \"agent noun\" (such as adding 'r' to 'bite' in English produces 'biter').<ref>{{PE|13}} p. 141</ref><ref>{{HH|Death}}, note 6, p. 564</ref>\n\n{{references}}\n{{weapons}}\n\n[[Category:Arrows]]\n[[Category:Noldorin names]]\n\n[[de:Dailir]]\n[[fr:encyclo:artefacts:armes:dailir]]\n[[fi:Dailir]]"}}}